<br>
[Thu Jul 19 21:49:12 2001] Maltyn says, 'Well he saw that the guard could only have what could be Blackburrow Stout!  '<br>
[Thu Jul 19 21:49:55 2001] Maltyn says, 'Dreezl stood quietly...breathing soflty as to draw no attention to himself.'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 21:50:21 2001] Maltyn says, 'Of course they were well intoxicated by this time, but Dreezil never became complacent'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 21:50:35 2001] Maltyn says, 'This was one of his strongest qualities as a rogue'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 21:50:52 2001] Maltyn says, 'He was not lazy about being careful of his movements and actions'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 21:51:12 2001] Maltyn says, 'He watched as first one....then the other of the guards began to nod their heads'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 21:52:00 2001] Maltyn says, 'And as each drifted into a deep sleep he crept closer..stopping occasionally to make sure they were sleeping as was evidenced by their snoring piercing the nite'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 21:52:33 2001] Maltyn says, 'When he felt the time was right he moved in slowly to where they were and picked up the large skin sack he had seen'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 21:53:10 2001] Maltyn says, 'He looked inside slowly and picked out the still full bottles of Blackburrow Stout...holding as many as he could in his little halfling hands and arms'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 21:53:55 2001] Maltyn says, 'He thought to himself...now I have the evidence that I need.  These guards were corrupt...and if I can expose them...what a reward their must be!'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 21:54:31 2001] Maltyn says, 'Dreezil salivated just a bit at the thought of rewards and riches they would no doubt place upon him...'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 21:56:12 2001] Maltyn says, 'He slowly turned and headed toward the castle entrance, smiling to himself.  Looking upon the first tall human he encountered and open his mouth to speak of the guards actions when he heard a startled SQUAWK!@!!'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 21:56:25 2001] Maltyn says, 'and the guards yelling behind him'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 21:56:43 2001] Maltyn says, 'AHA!!! Now I have found you, you smuggling thief!!'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 21:57:06 2001] Maltyn says, 'Carson Mccabe will be pleased to hear that you were so considerate as to walk right into the castle and give yourself up!'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 21:58:42 2001] Maltyn says, 'Dreezil was in a predicament as the very evidence he was going to use against the guards was being used against him!'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 21:59:19 2001] Maltyn says, 'They began to drag him into the castle protesting and struggling all the way'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:01:12 2001] Maltyn says, 'Well...they took him before Carson McCabe, but transferred eight bottles of the stout to a wooden case leaving the rest in their private chambers'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:01:46 2001] Maltyn says, 'When they arrived Carsn looked closely at Dreezil and recognized the guild symbol on his collar'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:02:29 2001] Maltyn says, 'Having the sign of the Deeppockets clearly identifed him as a rogue and therefor to McCabe a scoundrel as well'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:03:14 2001] Maltyn says, 'He ignored the halflings protests of innocence and viewed the contents of the wooden case as proof of Dreezil's crime.  He sent the guards to confine Dreezil to the dungeon of Highkeep.'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:03:29 2001] Maltyn says, 'Should I stop now...does thou grow weary?'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:04:24 2001] Maltyn says, 'All right then...the guards took great pleasure in escorting the halfling rogue to the lower keep'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:15:33 2001] Maltyn says, 'The guards took great pleasure in chaining Dreezil up'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:16:29 2001] Maltyn says, 'They chained him with his hands spread far apart on the wall beside him...the standard practice for those with acknowledged pickpocket skills'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:16:57 2001] Maltyn says, 'Dreezil looked very forlorn in this dark dungeon as the great iron cell doors clanged shut...'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:17:23 2001] Maltyn says, 'The other half naked, smelly, sweating prisoners stared hopelesslt at him through sunken eyes'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:18:28 2001] Maltyn says, 'It was not untl the sun sank low and the darkness of the cell enclosed around him that he rezlized his predicament...it had not seemed possible that this could happen...but here he was and no idea what would happen next'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:19:32 2001] Maltyn says, 'He languished there in the prison as the days turned into weeks, the weeks into months until they seemed to meld into one long, endless, boring, miserable nightmare of existence'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:21:49 2001] Maltyn says, 'Well as Dreezil was eeking out existense in the dark cell...he could not help but hear the whisperings and pieces of conversations echoing through the dungeon that told him that something terrible was happening in the world'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:22:39 2001] Maltyn says, 'He heard rumors that Highhold was under attack and his hometown of Rivervale had been ransacked and taken over briefly.'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:23:20 2001] Maltyn says, 'He assumed from the sounds of revelry some unknown days later that things had worked out, evidently in favor of Carson McCabe and high Hold'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:23:58 2001] Maltyn says, 'Nevertheless he missed his family and feared what may have come upon them in his absense and this attack on Rivervale'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:25:00 2001] Maltyn says, 'This only added to his ceaseless misery'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:25:30 2001] Maltyn says, 'Unbeknown to Dreezil was that his fortune was about to change...but from and unexpected source'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:26:38 2001] Maltyn says, 'You see there was one known as Firiona Via and Sionachie that had traveled many weeks across Antonica, finally arriving in Rivervale in search of young Dreezil'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:27:32 2001] Maltyn says, 'They came upon Wurrin and Teezil in a burrow not far from the inn, known as Fools Gold.  Perhaps you have seen the place?'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:28:23 2001] Maltyn says, 'Well Firiona thought is was a fitting name for an establishment that encouraged gambling and housed the local rogues guild'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:29:15 2001] Maltyn says, 'In either case Teezil and Wurrin welcomed the Paladin warmly'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:30:17 2001] Maltyn says, 'Welcome t' our home me lady, the diminuative woman smiled up at firiona and amiled, scurrying to find the largest chair to offer her'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:30:45 2001] Maltyn says, 'Me 'hasband an' me we've heard a great deal about ye lately'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:31:03 2001] Maltyn says, 'Tis said ye defeated th' Child o'Hate in Kithicor, it is'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:31:42 2001] Maltyn says, 'Wurrin her husband coughed slightly and nodded'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:31:50 2001] Maltyn says, 'A gentlemen of few words was Wurrin'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:32:05 2001] Maltyn says, 'He pulled out a briar pipe and bagan to pack it with tobacco'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:32:28 2001] Maltyn says, 'He listened as his wife rambled on and watched teh beautiful high elf lady from uder his beetled brow'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:33:04 2001] Maltyn says, 'Firiona responded kindly and thanked Teezil and Wurrin for their hospitality and smiled.'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:33:33 2001] Maltyn says, 'I was hoping you would be able to offer a bit of information as well? replied Firiona...her face begininging to cloud with concern'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:34:40 2001] Maltyn says, 'At this point Wurrin her husban sat up sharply...puffing sharply on his pipe and slowly blowing blue white smike in tiny rings'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:35:48 2001] Maltyn says, 'Really, me lady? What kind o' information mich sech as we have f'r ye? Teezil folded her hands across her apron as she stared puzzled at the high elf lady'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:36:16 2001] Maltyn says, 'Firiona said, It concerns your son Dreezil....'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:36:44 2001] Maltyn says, 'Teezils eys grew wide and Wurrin blew another set of smoke rings high into the air'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:37:32 2001] Maltyn says, 'Dreezil has been a companion of mine in the past as you know, and i would find him again. I have missed his ready wit and his skils wiht locks are second to none'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:37:59 2001] Maltyn says, 'In my travels it would be useful to have one of his abilites nearby and the Lady Tunare has charged me with gathering up my companions'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:38:20 2001] Maltyn says, 'I have not been able to find Dreezil's whereabouts which is not unusual for a rogue <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> '<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:38:39 2001] Maltyn says, 'But I thought I would pay you a visit to see if you could direct me where he might be found'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:39:26 2001] Maltyn says, 'Teezil's eyes began to mist over and she blinked twice, a tear falling soflty down her cheek'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:40:06 2001] Maltyn says, 'He was arrested in Highkeep, my'lady..they tell me'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:40:37 2001] Maltyn says, 'For smugglin' I KNOW my Dreezil wouldnae do sech a thin', 'tis nae possible'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:40:50 2001] Maltyn says, 'I jus' know it. He's a good boy, 'e is'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:41:19 2001] Maltyn says, 'Meith you speak with great insight'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:41:50 2001] Maltyn says, 'As they were speaking Carson McCabe himself stood at the thron room in Highkeep'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:42:28 2001] Maltyn says, 'He looked around at his chamberlain and advisors, listening to them recount the myriad of problems that were his to resolve during his afternoon session'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:43:01 2001] Maltyn says, 'Little was he to know that his afternoon would have very different results than he could ever have imagined'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:45:04 2001] Maltyn says, 'Ahh Dreezil...'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:45:35 2001] Maltyn says, 'As Carson McCabe was talking to his advisors about to begin his afternoon sessions they heard a commotion at the door to the chambers'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:46:20 2001] Maltyn says, 'Two guards opened the door and ushered in a familar high elf woman and her half elf friend.  Carson smiled.'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:47:10 2001] Maltyn says, 'Firiona! How good to see you! And this must be Sionachie. I ahve heard of your ability with the madolin my dear and your excellent singing voice!'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:47:31 2001] Maltyn says, 'I certainly hope you plan on staying and favoring us with a song or two'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:47:47 2001] Maltyn says, 'Sionachie blushed and smiled.  Thank you for your kind welcome and words'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:48:12 2001] Maltyn says, 'But I believe Firiona has some urgent business to attend to...Firiona nodded'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:48:53 2001] Maltyn says, 'Yes that is true, Carson.  You see I am looking for a certain halfling lad by the name of Dreezil'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:49:09 2001] Maltyn says, 'I understand he was here in Highpass...would you know anything about it?'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:49:49 2001] Maltyn says, 'Carson looked over to Arvelion, his chamberlain.  The man's bald head gleamed with sweat as he stepped up to answer'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:50:12 2001] Maltyn says, 'His heavy jailring key rattled with the keys on it about his neck'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:50:32 2001] Maltyn says, 'Yes sire. I beleive that is the name of the smuggler we arrested and have in our dungeon'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:50:43 2001] Maltyn says, 'Caught em red-handed we did'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:51:44 2001] Maltyn says, 'Firiona raised both of her eyebrows and stared with steel eyes at the man, who narrow mustache and sparse beard appeared very black against his now pale face.  she waited for him to continue.'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:52:36 2001] Maltyn says, 'He was carrying the contraband on himn when he was caught!! He said earnestly'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:53:22 2001] Maltyn says, 'In fact I locked it up in the stores myself!  Sweat began to trickle down his forehead.  Firiona continued to stare direclty at him...her gaze unwavering'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:55:51 2001] Maltyn says, 'go bring this halfing here, Carson said in a stern voice...let me see for myself'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:56:33 2001] Maltyn says, 'There you see...we caught him red handed, said the chamberlain.  His face was very flush by exertion and his ernest assertions'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:57:04 2001] Maltyn says, 'Firiona peered at the so called evidence and held a bottle up to the light'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:57:22 2001] Maltyn says, 'YEs it does indeed appear to be blackburrow stout, as she lowered the bottle back into the case'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:57:43 2001] Maltyn says, 'You say my little friend smuggled this?  How long is his jail sentence?'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:58:09 2001] Maltyn says, 'Carson's btow furrowed....Sentence?? Hell sit down there until he rots as far as I am concered!'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:58:24 2001] Maltyn says, 'Rogues like that are not to be trusted...particularly halflings!'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 22:59:31 2001] Maltyn says, 'Firionas expression grew bland and she tilted her head to one side...No trial has been had yet?'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 23:00:20 2001] Maltyn says, 'TRIAL!! said Carson with such laughter that it shook the bottles in the case...for a HALFLING SMUGGLER?!?!?  I will not waste my time!'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 23:01:08 2001] Maltyn says, 'Firiona's eyelids lowered slightly and her voice was very soft as she spoke'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 23:02:09 2001] Maltyn says, 'Then perhaps I can arrange for a judge to come here and hear his case. I will represent him myself. He can have a jury as well.  I know you are a fair and honorbale man, McCabe. And I know you to be just, as well.'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 23:02:20 2001] Maltyn says, 'It will be no trouble at all. I will see to everything personally'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 23:02:59 2001] Maltyn says, 'Carson sputtered and spat as his face turned a deep shade of crimson.'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 23:03:11 2001] Maltyn says, 'Oh dear, if you must firiona, then you must'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 23:06:09 2001] Maltyn says, 'Firiona responded kindly and said Nonsense Carson!  Id be happy to do it in the interest of justice.'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 23:06:31 2001] Maltyn says, 'She smiled sweetly and looked toward the case of stout...you dont mind if I take this for safekeeping?'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 23:07:15 2001] Maltyn says, 'Carson's puzzled frown disappeared in a resigned smile when he could think of no reason to deny her andhe nodded his assent'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 23:07:43 2001] Maltyn says, 'Certainly my dear!  Dont drink it all in one sitting now!  He chuckled at his own joke'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 23:08:51 2001] Maltyn says, 'Three days later Firiona had assembled 12 jurors from the surrounding countryside and the visiting judge, a retired soldier, Furgly Wiggins in the great hall of High Keep Castle'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 23:09:34 2001] Maltyn says, 'Avelion had been appointed as the prosection and Firiona was prepared with her defense'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 23:10:11 2001] Maltyn says, 'Furley, a grizzled veteran of many battles, was sitting comfortably in a velvet cushioned chair behind a large table'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 23:10:46 2001] Maltyn says, 'Two guards walked in with Dreezil between the, his wrists bound to a length of wood that he carried upon his shoulders'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 23:11:46 2001] Maltyn says, 'Dreezil, looked pained and a dejected expression was upon his face that was normally cheerful'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 23:13:47 2001] Maltyn says, 'Judge Wiggins pulled a dagger from his belt and rapped the table with the base of its hilt'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 23:15:19 2001] Maltyn says, 'Citizens I would like to finish the story....but the citizens of the server are calling quite loudly now and I must give them some attention'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 23:15:59 2001] Maltyn says, 'Can we finish the story this Saturday evening...perhaps around 5pm PST?'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 23:17:06 2001] Maltyn says, 'OK back here Saturday at 5pm PST then...hat is 6pm MST&lt; 7pm CST, 8pm EST'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 23:18:06 2001] Maltyn says, 'I thank you for your attentive ears and hope to see you back Saturday..tell others that Dreezil is about to be tried and his advocate is Firiona herself'<br>
[Thu Jul 19 23:18:28 2001] Maltyn says, 'Be well citizens'<br>
