<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:05:57 2001] Maltyn says, 'The name of the Judge was Wiggins I do beleive'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:06:15 2001] Maltyn says, 'and he said...Settle down, now, settle down!'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:06:24 2001] Maltyn says, 'He tried to get the attention of the assembly'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:07:02 2001] Maltyn says, 'The jurors murmered as they settled in their seats...Firiona stood quietly and watched while the room grew queit and then stepped forward'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:08:02 2001] Maltyn says, 'Your Honor...I want to thank you for allowing us to present this case before you, and for taking the time to travel here from Rivervale for this purpose. If you will permit me, I woul like to explain the details of the case before you today'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:09:37 2001] Maltyn says, 'Dreezil Pocketdip here who is a resident of Rivervale and is an ackknowledged member of the Deeppockeyts guild there has been accused of smuggling'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:09:56 2001] Maltyn says, 'To be more precise, he is accused of smuggling one case of Blackburrow stout.'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:11:35 2001] Maltyn says, 'ahh yes...His accusers are int he courtroom today as is Dreezil himself'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:12:48 2001] Maltyn says, 'your honor, I beleive what has happened here is that the defendent has been accused strictly on the basis of circumstantial evidence - evidence which in and of itself, is not sufficient to demonstrate the commission of any crime'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:13:36 2001] Maltyn says, 'As the defendants counsel, Your Honor, I will be attempting to show how the vents occurred which led to Dreezils arrest and inarceration'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:14:12 2001] Maltyn says, 'I beleive the Jury will see that Dreezil was not involved in smuggling, but rather, was attempting to assist the authorities here in High Hold Pass in their efforts to end smuggling.'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:14:42 2001] Maltyn says, 'furthermore, I will try to demonstrate that there are in fact other parties involved in inferious and illegal activities right here in Highkeep'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:15:34 2001] Maltyn says, 'The onlookers then began to murmur amongst themselves at this revelation'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:16:05 2001] Maltyn says, 'Firiona looked over at Carson Mcabe and noted with satisfaction the mild look of surprise on his face'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:16:41 2001] Maltyn says, 'She turned back to the judge and said, your honor, I think you for allowing us to appear before you today.'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:17:02 2001] Maltyn says, 'The high elf sat down and folded her hands in her lap, looing over at Arvelion'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:17:20 2001] Maltyn says, 'The chamberlain/prosecuter stood up and faced the jury...'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:18:01 2001] Maltyn says, 'It is very simple ladies and gentlemen...this halfling rogue (said with obvious distaste) was caught with evidence in his hand just outside Highkeep.'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:18:37 2001] Maltyn says, 'After I have produced my witnesses and you have heard their testimony, there will be no doubt in you minds that he is indeed guilty of smuggling blackburrow stout'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:19:22 2001] Maltyn says, 'I am certain you will see your way clear to finding him guilty as charged and this rogue deserves to be punished for her crimer and activities.'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:19:39 2001] Maltyn says, 'I thank you too, your honor and members of the jury for allowing us to appear before you.'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:20:09 2001] Maltyn says, 'He turned back to Firiona and smirked, smuggly anticipating his easy victory'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:21:38 2001] Sayah says, 'Your honor I would like to present you the evidence .'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:21:41 2001] Maltyn says, 'There is a certain case of Blackburrow stout in the possession of the defendant's counsel that I would ask she produce at this time'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:22:56 2001] Maltyn says, 'Arvelion sneered at Firiona.'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:23:19 2001] Maltyn says, 'She returned his glance blandly and stood, easily lifting the wooden case and carrying it over to the judge's bench'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:24:12 2001] Maltyn says, 'At the prosecution's request, I present to you the case of blackburrow stout into evidence at this time'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:24:48 2001] Maltyn says, 'The judge looked down, one eye blinking slightly. He montioned to Firiona to place the case on the floor near his seat, behind the bench'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:25:12 2001] Maltyn says, 'Very well, said Judge Wiggins.'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:25:28 2001] Maltyn says, 'It can remain here until it can be properly identified by witnesses'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:25:47 2001] Maltyn says, 'He peered down at this side where the case lay just out of sight behind his bench'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:26:03 2001] Maltyn says, 'Firiona smiled and returned to her seat'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:26:24 2001] Maltyn says, 'Now then said Arvelion, I would like to call one Guard Heptal to the stand if you please'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:26:50 2001] Maltyn says, 'a Tall guardsman moved to the front of the courteoom and took his place in front of the jury'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:30:09 2001] Maltyn says, 'Judge Wiggins looked down glaringly from his bench at Guard Heptal and said, you must speak the truth by your oath of fealty and your honor as a guardsman, do you understand?'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:30:57 2001] Maltyn says, 'Heptal nodded quickly.'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:31:17 2001] Maltyn says, 'Arvelion faced him and cleared this throat delicately before beginning'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:31:53 2001] Maltyn says, 'Heptal, please tell us under what circumstances you met the accused, if you would?'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:32:22 2001] Maltyn says, 'The tall guards face reddend slightly as he was not accustomed to speaking in public'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:33:00 2001] Maltyn says, 'Well ou see...I was comin out of the gate to take my place of duty, y'know'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:33:25 2001] Maltyn says, 'Walkin' up t' th' gates and grinnin''<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:33:53 2001] Maltyn says, 'so I says to m'self, I says, hmmmm...somehin's funny about that one, I just know it'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:37:03 2001] Maltyn says, 'So I walks up to him and I says HOLD!!! Tat's what we says to strangers ya know.  So he stops and i looks and sure enough, there he is, big as day, holdin' a case o' Blackburrow Stout, he was!'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:37:28 2001] Maltyn says, 'I know that's got to be smuggled, sinc it isnt legal here in Highkeep or parts hereabouts'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:37:56 2001] Maltyn says, 'So I takes and arrests him, your lordship sir.'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:38:13 2001] Maltyn says, 'And there he sits, plain as day, right over there.  He points at Dreezil'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:44:23 2001] Maltyn says, 'Dreezil frowned unhapppily'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:44:44 2001] Maltyn says, 'The judge ducked down behind his bench, momentarily out of sigh of all the onlookers.'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:45:10 2001] Maltyn says, 'A tiny pop and hiss could be heard if you were close enough, though no one but Dreezil actually was'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:45:37 2001] Maltyn says, 'He tilted his head to one side slightly and looked over puzzled'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:46:37 2001] Maltyn says, 'The judge popped back up and Dreezil could see a slight flush on his face from the close distance'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:47:29 2001] Maltyn says, 'Arvelion continued...How did he say he had come by the contraband Heptal? Would you please tell the court?'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:47:53 2001] Maltyn says, 'Well, um...Heptal hesitated...'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:48:39 2001] Maltyn says, 'I didnt exaclty...er...well, y'see, I didn't question him m'self, y'know. I took himt'Carson Macabe y'see, an' he told me t' put th' rogue in a cell, is what happened, y'know.'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:49:05 2001] Maltyn says, 'but the only place he could've got it is from some gnoll in blackburrow o'course'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:49:30 2001] Maltyn says, 'Everbody knows where it comes from y'see, and' so that's where he must've got it'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:49:50 2001] Maltyn says, 'Have you ever seen this kind of contrband before, Heptal?'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:50:47 2001] Maltyn says, 'Yup, I sure have, yer chamberlainship, I sure have. They always runnin it through the pass, those gnolls, That Guurich, o'er in Misty Thickey, he's part o' this, y';can count on it, y'can'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:51:27 2001] Maltyn says, 'So you are somewhat of an expert on this smuggling ring, then eh, Heptal?'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:52:00 2001] Maltyn says, 'The guard preened visibly, I am at that y'know. Yes I am!'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:52:27 2001] Maltyn says, 'Arvelion smiled and turned to Firiona. You may cross examin if you wish m'ylady'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:53:19 2001] Maltyn says, 'firiona stood up and walked over to Guard Heptal.'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:54:07 2001] Maltyn says, 'Thank you Arvelion, and thank you too, Guard Heptal, for your expert witness here today. I see you have had a lot of experience uncovering and breaking smuggling rings, eh?'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:54:33 2001] Maltyn says, 'Heptal grinned back...openly admiring Firiona.'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:55:16 2001] Maltyn says, 'Yes, my'lady, if I do say so m'self, I have probably done more than any other guard in Highkeep t'keep things sage that way. Yep. That's what I'd say.'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:55:40 2001] Maltyn says, 'You said you saw the defendant heading toward the gates when you first saw him correct?'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:56:42 2001] Maltyn says, 'Heptal nodded enthusiastically. Yep, That's what he was doin. Headin' right toward th' gate. Funniest thing I ever saw. Him smugglin' an' headin' right toward a guard. He chuckled..'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:57:09 2001] Maltyn says, 'Do you often see smugglers walking right up to the gates with incriminating evidence in their hands for you to seize?'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:57:55 2001] Maltyn says, 'Heptal looked a bit confused. Well, no, o'course not my'lady.That's what's so funny about it. He just walked right up and let me arrest him. Oddest thing I ever seen, it was.'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:58:32 2001] Maltyn says, 'As he spoke, the judge chortled to himself softly. He ducked his head uner his desk again for a moment or two while all eyes wee on Firiona dn the witness'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:59:28 2001] Maltyn says, 'Firiona continued....Did it occur to you that perhaps ther might be something more to the defendants presence than met the eye?'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 20:59:39 2001] Maltyn says, 'that perhaps he was not in fact a smuggler'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:01:15 2001] Maltyn says, 'That perhaps he was not in fact smuggling, but rather that he might have been attempting to produce evidence against some other perpertrator'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:02:33 2001] Maltyn says, 'Te guard stammered then coughed a little.'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:02:56 2001] Maltyn says, 'well nom my'lady, o' course it didnt. He is a rogue after all. I mean you can see he wears the guild emblem.'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:03:19 2001] Maltyn says, 'Rogues dont helpt he guards y'know'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:03:49 2001] Maltyn says, 'He laughed in wonder, trying to imagine anyone not knowing that'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:06:08 2001] Maltyn says, 'So you assumed then that since Dreezil was a rogue he also was a smuggler, is that it?'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:06:26 2001] Maltyn says, 'Of course it is! Heptal looked at Firiona in surpised confusion.'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:07:28 2001] Maltyn says, 'Judge Wiggins leaned down behind his bench for a bit and came back up with his face flushed red. He put his hand over his mouth to muffle a belch.'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:08:10 2001] Maltyn says, 'Firiona looked over and grinned slighly. She nodded to herself and turned back to Arvelion. Would you care to cross-examine, Lord Chamberlain?'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:08:45 2001] Maltyn says, 'Why firiona, I thin the prosecution has made its case rather well already, thank you. The Chamberlian smiled down his nose at firiona'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:10:14 2001] Maltyn says, 'That will be all, you may step down.'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:10:38 2001] Maltyn says, 'Firiona watched as Guard Heptal stepped down and march back to his seat on the front bench.'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:10:53 2001] Maltyn says, 'She then turned to the judge and said, At this time I'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:11:08 2001] Maltyn says, 'would lke to call CArson Mccabe to the stadn, your Honor'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:11:44 2001] Maltyn says, 'Carson moved up to the witness stand and stood quietly'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:12:16 2001] Maltyn says, 'The judge nodded at him and said You knowth tha'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:12:37 2001] Maltyn says, 'you mus' spek th' truth, 'ere, an' nothin' els' eigh'?'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:13:07 2001] Maltyn says, 'Carson frowned up at the judge, but only nodded his compliance'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:13:52 2001] Maltyn says, 'Judge Wiggins smiled blearily and ducked down behind his bench for a moment. Carson's frown mad ean upside-down V in the skin over his nose'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:15:18 2001] Maltyn says, 'Firiona stepped up to Carson Mccabe, distrcting him. Carson, do you recall the occasion on which ou first saw the defendant?'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:16:42 2001] Maltyn says, 'Well as you can see...this went back and forth between CArson and Firiona for some time...both to the reason why he was incarcerated without a trial, held in a dungeon trained etc'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:17:09 2001] Maltyn says, 'Carson became more and more angry with each question till he was literally shouting his answers back spitefullt at Firiona'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:18:01 2001] Maltyn says, 'She asked one final question...Did you Carson McCabe examine the evidence yourself?'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:18:22 2001] Maltyn says, 'He angrily answered NO!!! I did not'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:18:44 2001] Maltyn says, 'She replied then, then you dont truly know what was in the case is that correct?'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:19:12 2001] Maltyn says, 'Yes THAT IS CORRECT!'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:19:31 2001] Maltyn says, 'Carsons sheepish expression fitted him oddly'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:19:56 2001] Maltyn says, 'Firiona smiled at her friend, Dreezil.'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:20:23 2001] Maltyn says, 'Well perhaps we shoudl take a moment to look at the evidence in question at this time.  Your honor...'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:20:39 2001] Maltyn says, 'Firiona looked up at the empty bench...Your honor?????'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:21:01 2001] Maltyn says, 'Firiona approached the bench and walked around it to the other side where the case of stout had been sittting'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:21:18 2001] Maltyn says, 'The judge suddenly popped back into view...his face red and grinning'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:21:27 2001] Maltyn says, 'Yesh, what izh it?'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:21:33 2001] Maltyn says, 'teh judge slurred'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:21:50 2001] Maltyn says, 'He reached down and lifted the wooden box up which rattled loudly'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:22:08 2001] Maltyn says, 'Firiona quicly grabbed it, fearing it would fall'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:22:15 2001] Maltyn says, 'She placed it atop the desk and looked over it'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:22:43 2001] Maltyn says, 'All the others had been emptied'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:23:02 2001] Maltyn says, 'She peered up at the judge, her expression bland'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:23:29 2001] Maltyn says, 'She picked up the remains and took them over to  Carson...is this the  case you saw the defendant carrying?'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:24:19 2001] Maltyn says, 'Well I didnt actually see him with it...the guards told me that he had ot'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:25:00 2001] Maltyn says, 'Firiona picked up the box and carried it over to Dreezil and placed it on the ground'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:25:37 2001] Maltyn says, 'It was easy to see that the halfling would have a difficult time carrying even a few full ceramic bottles of the potent brew in a heavey wooden box like this'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:26:07 2001] Maltyn says, 'Firiona asked that Dreezil be unshackeled'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:26:18 2001] Maltyn says, 'She then instructed Dreezil to pick up the box'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:26:51 2001] Maltyn says, 'Dreezil knelt at the knees and tried to reach the sides of the box to pick it up...but his short arms just would not reach'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:27:23 2001] Maltyn says, 'Try as he might he could not get his arms around the box to pick it up!'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:28:05 2001] Maltyn says, 'Firiona said...you see your honor, Dreezil could not have very well carrie this box now could he?'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:29:02 2001] Maltyn says, 'With this new light and evidence the Judge stood, pounded his  dagger hilt on the table and Yelled ORDER!'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:29:27 2001] Maltyn says, 'This is not a case of smuggling, but a clear case of a frame up based on circumstantial evidence!'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:30:20 2001] Maltyn says, 'I hereby release Dreezil and order that he be compensated for his time being held against his will in these dungeons'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:30:48 2001] Maltyn says, 'This shall come from the treasury of Highkeep. Dreezil you are free to go!'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:31:12 2001] Maltyn says, 'A resounding cheer went up around the courtroom as Dreezil was in shock'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:31:45 2001] Maltyn says, 'Dreezil and Firiona walked out of the courtroom hand in hand'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:33:23 2001] Maltyn says, 'Or you may find him in the company of Firiona'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:33:58 2001] Maltyn says, 'I hope you enjoyed this <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> '<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:34:14 2001] Maltyn says, 'Dont judge a book by its cover, unless it is a DE of Neriak <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> '<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:34:29 2001] Maltyn chuckles at Twiggii.<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:34:44 2001] Maltyn says, 'tis my pleasure...be safe my friends'<br>
[Sat Jul 21 21:35:09 2001] Maltyn thanks everyone for coming.<br>
